        "timestamp": "2017-07-27 20:00:16.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nTom - good comment, thank you.\nI made some changes:\n\n\nThe intent of these \"populate seed code\" changes were just to move the seed code from the sdnc project over to the correct corresponding ccsdk repos. However,  some things were brought over that should not have been:\n\n - vnfapi and vnftools really belong in SDNC. not CCSDK.  They were added here by mistake (I just copied sdnc/northbound and missed pruning those).\n- capacity-api was not part of the openECOMP sdnc seed code, so it should come in as a separate change.\n\nI got rid of those 3 subdirectories (capacity-api, vnf-api and vnftools), so at this point this should be a pretty clean copy over of seed code from one project to another.  I'd prefer not to split it up into separate changes if we can avoid it, just to avoid the extra overhead, but if the committers feel it should be split further I can make that change.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
